# Python Notebooks

This folder contains the Jupyter notebooks developed for the cybersecurity threat detection capstone project.

The notebooks are organized into two main sections:

## EDA

The `EDA` folder contains notebooks for data cleaning, preprocessing, and exploratory data analysis across the three cybersecurity datasets.

Main analysis areas include:

- Missing value checks
- Duplicate checks
- Feature distribution analysis
- Univariate analysis
- Bivariate analysis
- Multivariate analysis
- Correlation heatmaps
- Class imbalance review
- Dataset quality comparison

## ML MODELS

The `ML MODELS` folder contains notebooks for supervised machine learning and unsupervised anomaly detection.

Main modeling areas include:

- Classification models
- Regression baseline experiments
- Model evaluation
- Confusion matrices
- ROC-AUC comparison
- Feature importance
- Clustering and anomaly detection

## Data Note

The raw datasets are not included in this repository.  
The notebooks were developed using public cybersecurity datasets and selected outputs are included for portfolio review.
